18/06/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The ambassadors of EU member states reaffirmed their countries' readiness to assist Montenegro on its road to Euro-Atlantic integration, during talks with Montenegrin Prime Minister Zeljko Sturanovic on Friday (June 15th). 
The meeting was held at the initiative of German envoy Thomas Schmitt, whose country currently holds the rotating EU presidency. 
The EU envoys said they expect Montenegro's new constitution will be approved soon, confirming the country's European course. 
(Vijesti, Pobjeda - 16/06/07; RTCG - 15/06/07)
